The paper deals with the problem of recovering point sources from low-pass measurements, which is a common problem in electronic imaging, optics, microscopy, and line spectral estimations. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the use of Fourier measurements and total variation norm in the optimization problem suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories of cs.SI (Signal Processing) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of numerical simulations and theoretical guarantees suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NA (Numerical Analysis).
